function getUniqueRandomNumbers(count, upperLimit)
  local randomNumbers = {}
  repeat
    local currentRandomNumber = math.random(upperLimit)
    -- print("CurrentRandomNumber: " .. currentRandomNumber)
    if #randomNumbers > 0 then
      if table.contains(randomNumbers, currentRandomNumber) == false then
        table.insert(randomNumbers, #randomNumbers+1, currentRandomNumber)
      end
    else
      table.insert(randomNumbers, #randomNumbers+1, currentRandomNumber)
    end
    -- print("CurrentRandomNumberCount: " .. #randomNumbers)
    -- print( math.random(upperLimit))
  until #randomNumbers == count
  return randomNumbers
end

function table.contains(table, element)
  for _, value in pairs(table) do
    if value == element then
      return true
    end
  end
  return false
end

function split(pString, pPattern)
   local Table = {}  -- NOTE: use {n = 0} in Lua-5.0
   local fpat = "(.-)" .. pPattern
   local last_end = 1
   local s, e, cap = pString:find(fpat, 1)
   while s do
      if s ~= 1 or cap ~= "" then
     table.insert(Table,cap)
      end
      last_end = e+1
      s, e, cap = pString:find(fpat, last_end)
   end
   if last_end <= #pString then
      cap = pString:sub(last_end)
      table.insert(Table, cap)
   end
   return Table
end

function printAnnouncement(message)
  print("") --newline
  print("===============================================================")
  print(message)
  print("===============================================================")
  print("") --newline
end

function lookupEncounterTable(message, playerColor)
  local numbers = {} -- EncounterTable, EncounterNumber
  local numberIndex = 1

  if string.match(message, "%+") == "+" then
    -- print("found +")
    local splitMessage = split(message, "%+") --split 10+1
    if splitMessage == nil then print("splitMessage is NIL") return end
    -- print("#splitMessage: " .. #splitMessage)
    if #splitMessage > 1 then
      message = splitMessage[1]
      for i=2, #splitMessage do
        message = message .. " " .. splitMessage[i]
      end
    end
  end

  for number in string.gmatch(message, "%S+") do
    -- print("Number found! " .. number)
    if tonumber(number) ~= nil then
      if numberIndex == 2 and tonumber(number) > 12 then break end
      numbers[numberIndex] = tonumber(number)
      numberIndex = numberIndex + 1
    end
  end

  -- for i,v in ipairs(numbers) do print(i,v) end
  local encounterTableNumber = numbers[1]
  if encounterTableNumber ~= nil then --encounter table number is number, and exists
    if PrintableEncounterTableTitles[encounterTableNumber] == nil then
      printAnnouncement("My most sincere apologies. It seems that encounter has been lost to the sands of time..")
      return true
    else
      print("") --newline
      print("==============================")
      print("Encounter Table: " .. PrintableEncounterTableTitles[encounterTableNumber])
      print("----------------------------------------")
      local selectedEncounterTable = PrintableEncounterTables[encounterTableNumber]
      local encounterNumber = numbers[2]
      if encounterNumber == nil then
        -- print("Encounter Number is NIL")
        for i,v in ipairs(selectedEncounterTable) do
          print(v["Text"])
        end
      else
        -- print("Encounter Number Found!")
        CurrentEncounter = selectedEncounterTable[encounterNumber]
        print(CurrentEncounter["Text"])
        showReactionButtons(playerColor)
      end
      print("==============================")
    end
    return true
  end--ignore if NOT a number
end

function showReactionButtons(playerColor)
  local currentReactionLetter = CurrentEncounter["ReactionMatrix"]
  local availableReactions = Reactions[currentReactionLetter]

  -- print("PlayerColor: " .. playerColor)

  local playerCharacter = PlayerCharacters[playerColor]
  if playerCharacter == nil then print("Please select a character to play") return end

  -- print("PlayerCharacter: " .. PlayerCharacters[playerColor])

  local playerBoard = getObjectFromGUID(PlayerBoardGuids[PlayerCharacters[playerColor]])
  local xOffset = 4

  CurrentReactionPlayerColor = playerColor
  clearPlayerButtons(CurrentReactionPlayerColor)

  if availableReactions == nil then print("Reactions unavailable for: " .. currentReactionLetter) return end

  for i,v in ipairs(availableReactions) do
    local functionName = "reaction" .. v
    playerBoard.createButton({click_function=functionName,
                              label=v,
                              position={xOffset,0.6,-5.5},
                              rotation={0,90,0},
                              font_size=200,
                              width=1600,
                              height=400})
    xOffset = xOffset - 1
  end
end

function resolveReaction(message)
  if CurrentEncounter ~= nil then
    local reactionTable = ReactionTables[CurrentEncounter["ReactionMatrix"]]
    if reactionTable == nil then print("Reaction table is nil") return end
    -- print("Reaction Table: " .. reactionTable)
    local reactions = reactionTable[CurrentEncounter["Characteristic"]]
    if reactions == nil then print("Reactions is nil for " .. CurrentEncounter["ReactionMatrix"] .. ": " .. CurrentEncounter["Characteristic"]) return end
    -- print("Reactions: " .. reactions)
    local reactionIndex = reactions[message]
    if reactionIndex == nil then return end
    printAnnouncement(message .. ": Please read passage " .. reactionIndex .. " ± destiny die result in the Book of Tales")
    clearPlayerButtons(CurrentReactionPlayerColor)
    -- print(ReactionTables[CurrentEncounter["ReactionMatrix"]][CurrentEncounter["Characteristic"]][message])
  end
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
local ConcealedStorageHeight = 3.0
local ConceiledStorageOffset = 10000.0
local StorageState = 1

local BB = {
	Min = {
		x = -16.0,
		y = 41.99,
		z = -50.0
	},
	Max = {
		x = 16.0,
		y = 41.99,
		z = -32.0
	}
}

function onLoad()
    self.interactable = false;
	
    self.createButton({
		label = "",
		click_function = "onButtonClick",
		function_owner = self,
		width = 1000,
		height = 750,
		color = {1, 0, 0, 0.0},
		position = {0, 40.7, 50.5},
		rotation = {-90, 0, 0},
		font_size = 200
    })
	
	if self.getStateId() ~= StorageState then
    Timer.create({
        identifier = ("onAfterLoad" .. self.guid),
        function_name = "onAfterLoad",
        delay = 0.2
    })
	end
end

function onAfterLoad()
	local pos = self.getPosition()
	local bounds = self.getBoundsNormalized()
	local rot = self.getRotation()
	local direction = 1.0
	
	if rot.y == 0 then
		direction = -1.0
	end
	
	BB.Min.x = BB.Min.x + pos.x
	BB.Min.y = BB.Min.y + pos.y - 1.5
	BB.Min.z = (BB.Min.z * direction) + pos.z
	
	BB.Max.x = 	BB.Max.x + pos.x
	BB.Max.y = 	BB.Max.y + pos.y + ConcealedStorageHeight + 0.5
	BB.Max.z = (BB.Max.z * direction) + pos.z
	
	HideObjectsAbove( false )
end

function onButtonClick()
	local currentState = self.getStateId()
	local nextState = 1 + (currentState % 2)
	
	if currentState ~= StorageState then
		HideObjectsAbove( true )
	end
	
	self.setState( nextState )
end

function HideObjectsAbove( toggle )
    local objectsAbove = {}
	local BBMin = { x = BB.Min.x, y = BB.Min.y, z = BB.Min.z }
	local BBMax = { x = BB.Max.x, y = BB.Max.y, z = BB.Max.z }
	
	if not toggle then
		BBMin.y = BBMin.y - ConceiledStorageOffset
		BBMax.y = BBMax.y - ConceiledStorageOffset
	end
    
    for k,v in pairs( getAllObjects() ) do
        if v != self then
            if PointToAABBIntersect( BBMin, BBMax, v.getPosition() ) then
                if toggle then
                    Store( v )
                else
                    Dispense( v )
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

-- Assumes ||min|| < ||max||
function PointToAABBIntersect( min, max, point )
    if IsInRange( point.x, min.x, max.x ) and
       IsInRange( point.y, min.y, max.y ) and
       IsInRange( point.z, min.z, max.z ) then
	   return true
    end
    
    return false
end

function IsInRange( value, a, b )
	local min = 0
	local max = 0
	
	if a > b then
		max = a
		min = b
	else
		max = b
		min = a
	end
	
	if value > min and value < max then
		return true
	end
	
	return false
end

function Store( obj )
	local pos = obj.getPosition()
	local isLocked = obj.getLock()
	
	obj.setVar( "LockStatus", isLocked )
	
    obj.interactable = false
    obj.setLock( true )
    obj.setPosition({
        x = pos.x,
        y = pos.y - ConceiledStorageOffset,
        z = pos.z
    })
end

function Dispense( obj )
	local pos = obj.getPosition()
	local originalLockStatus = obj.getVar( "LockStatus" )
	
    obj.setPosition({
        x = pos.x,
        y = pos.y + ConceiledStorageOffset,
        z = pos.z
    })
	
    obj.interactable = true
	
	if originalLockStatus ~= nil and originalLockStatus == true then
		obj.setLock( true )
	else
		obj.setLock( false )
	end
end

--[[
   moving marker
   created by Rodney
]]

-- customize variables
markerScale = 1
markerRemainingTime = 1

frameInterval = 0.01
rotationDegreePerFrame = 1

-- global variables
markerObject = nil
rotationTimerId = nil
fadeOutTimerId = nil

lastBottomLevel = 1.5

movingMarkerVersion = "2016092000"

-- constants
hidePosition = {0, -300, 0}
hideScale = {0.1, 0.1, 0.1}

-- events
function onLoad()
   initializeTimer()
   createObjects()
end

function onDestroy()
   removeTimers()
   deleteObjects()
end

function onCollisionEnter(info)
   updateBottomLevel(info.contact_points)
end

function onPickedUp(color)
   removeTimers()
   setMarker()
end

function onDropped()
   fadeOutMarker()
end

-- internal functions

function createObjects()
   markerObject = spawnObject({
         type = "Custom_Model",
         position = hidePosition,
         rotation = {0, 0, 0},
         scale = hideScale
   })

   markerObject.setCustomObject({
